reviewText: This keeps my 2 year old happy and entertained during longer car rides, so I'm a fan! This is pretty much the only show that keeps his attention for entire episodes and he will watch them over and over. This is also one of the only shows made for toddlers that doesn't drive me crazy if I have to watch it or hear it a million times!

My daughter loves all things Mickey Mouse, and since we don't have cable we have to get the DVDs for her fix of her beloved "Mickey". There are five episodes on the DVD:
1. Around the Clubhouse World
2. Donald and the Beanstalk
3. Goofy on Mars
4. Mickey's Hand Helpers
5. Pluto's Dinosaur Romp

I had hoped this DVD would be a little more educational than it is (especially with the Around the Clubhouse world episode) but it still does follow the normal format of asking the kids to help problem solve so it's definitely not awful, just not as educational as some of the other Mickey Mouse Clubhouse DVDs that are out there.  My daughter still loves this DVD though and Donald and the Beanstalk is one of her favorites.

Another hit for Mickey Mouse Clubhouse!!  This DVD has 5 episodes:
1. Around the Clubhouse World (a little longer than a standard episode, closer to 30 minutes)
2. Donald and the Beanstalk
3. Goofy on Mars
4. Mickey's Handy Helpers
5. Pluto's Dinosaur Romp

Another great compilation, and a complete lifesaver for road trips!  Our collection of Mickey Mouse Clubhouse DVDs has absolutely saved us during long trips in the car.  Our kids love watching an episode of Mickey Mouse Clubhouse every morning, and on car trips they get the treat of watching them on the car DVD player.  The worth of these DVDs (if your little one is a fan) is immeasurable while traveling!  We've gotten through hours and hours in the car, on planes, etc because of Mickey!

We got this one for my son because he's watched every MMCH DVD ad nauseum and we wanted something new. The DVD came with a little passport book (which is cute). My son watched the "Around the Clubhouse World" episode and loves it. He sings all the songs, and he runs around saying "Look, it's my passport!" whenever the characters get stamped. The other episodes on this DVD are some of his favorites. I can't tell you how many times he's watched Mickey's Handy Helpers  back to back. Great DVD!

The baby loves to watch this show, she gets excited when it comes on, there are lots of colors, and teaches a lot of activities.

You can climb the Eiffel Tower, and say "bonjour" to Donald and Daisy, rescue Goofy when he's adrift in Italy's Grand Canal, solve the riddle of Pete's Egyptian pyramid, meet a dancing dragon at the Great Wall of China.  With your child's help, Clubhouse friends meet a dragon at Great Wall of China. And with Mouseketools, Clubhouse friends get their passports stamped at each place.  This two hour video has fun songs and 4 extra episodes, and  proves "It's
a small world after all".  This DVD comes with a passport activity booklet.  It's a fun show for kids and their parents.

My 4 yo grandson has been in love with Mickey Clubhouse for the last couple of years. All the videos I have purchased have been great! He has a small DVD player of his own, so he can watch his favorite videos and the rest of the family can watch something else on the TV. Worth every penny!

It's cute, but I wish I had picked a different Mickey Mouse for my son. He loves it, but I felt it was insensitive to the portrayed cultures at best. You're not going to have a wholesome culture experience with Mickey, who tends to follow mainstream American ideals, but it can be fun to watch with your child if you don't mind that.
